<title>BRAZIL: Brazil government considers appealing wage ruling.</title>
<headline>Brazil government considers appealing wage ruling.</headline>
<dateline>SAO PAULO 1997-02-20</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Brazilian government is studying a decision by the Supreme Court to award a pay rise of 28.9 percent to 11 civil servants to determine whether it should file an appeal, a government spokesman said.</p>
<p>&quot;The state attorney is studying the details of the Supreme Court decision to determine whether there should be an appeal,&quot; spokesman Sergio Amaral said in a statement.</p>
<p>President Fernando Henrique Cardoso reminded government ministers to refrain from making comments about judicial decisions, the statement added.</p>
<p>Brazilian stocks and Brady bonds fell after the court announcement on Wednesday on fears the measure could cost the federal government billions of dollars if it was extended to other public sector workers.</p>
<p>((--Joelle Diderich, Sao Paulo newsroom +55 11 248 5417))</p>
